{"title":"Thibaut Pinot and his goats have a casualwear range","link":"https://cyclingtips.com/2021/03/thibaut-pinot-and-his-goats-have-a-casualwear-range/","date":1616646980000,"content":"<p>Thibaut Pinot –&nbsp;the tragic hero of every French July since about 2014 – is known for many things. A Byronic charisma. A smouldering intensity. Very bad luck as a bicyclist. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>But of all the things about Pinot, one of the most surprising –&nbsp;and charming –&nbsp;is his collection of goats.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Let&#8217;s back up to March 2020, when the <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/kim.goat/\">Kim.Goat</a> Instagram page burst into life.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>There, Thibaut and his girlfriend, Andrea Vannier, catalogue a series of snapshots of their goats and their bucolic existence on the couple&#8217;s farm in Mélisey. “At the start of confinement, I went with my girlfriend to buy goat cheese,” Pinot <a href=\"https://www.archyde.com/cycling-i-want-to-go-to-the-end-of-my-story-says-thibaut-pinot/\">told</a> a curious interviewer last June. “I came back with two kids that we had to bottle feed. I had time.” <em>[I trust you can imagine the Gallic shrug, the insouciant pout, as he said that last line, because there’s no way it didn’t happen.]</em></p>\n\n\n\n<blockquote class=\"instagram-media\" data-instgrm-captioned=\"\" data-instgrm-permalink=\"https://www.instagram.com/p/B9_dP2iFJCR/?utm_source=ig_embed&amp;utm_campaign=loading\" data-instgrm-version=\"13\" style=\" background:#FFF; border:0; border-radius:3px; box-shadow:0 0 1px 0 rgba(0,0,0,0.5),0 1px 10px 0 rgba(0,0,0,0.15); margin: 1px; max-width:540px; min-width:326px; padding:0; width:99.375%; width:-webkit-calc(100% - 2px); width:calc(100% - 2px);\"><div style=\"padding:16px;\"> <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/p/B9_dP2iFJCR/?utm_source=ig_embed&amp;utm_campaign=loading\" style=\" background:#FFFFFF; line-height:0; padding:0 0; text-align:center; text-decoration:none; width:100%;\" target=\"_blank